# Base UI Design System Development Guide

## Overview

This guide provides a comprehensive implementation plan for building a design system similar to shadcn/ui using Base UI as the foundation. Base UI is a library of unstyled React UI components that provides complete control over your app's CSS and accessibility features, created by the makers of Radix, Floating UI, and Material UI.

## Project Architecture

### Core Philosophy
- **Unstyled Foundation**: Leverage Base UI's unstyled components for maximum customization
- **Copy-Paste Approach**: Follow shadcn/ui's model of providing ready-to-use component code
- **Framework Agnostic**: Support multiple CSS frameworks (Tailwind CSS, CSS Modules, Styled Components)
- **Accessibility First**: Built-in accessibility features from Base UI
- **Developer Experience**: CLI tool for easy component installation

